Tebogo Motlanthe, SAFA CEO during the 2021 SAFA Press Conference at the SAFA House, Johannesburg on the 22 January 2021 JOHANNESBURG - Tebogo Motlanthe has been appointed SAFA CEO on a permanent basis, after acting in the position for the past year. Motlanthe is familiar with SAFA’s Vision 2022, in which qualification for the FIFA World Cup in Qatar, is key. 